arts.ttl: With Gusto! France pull off comeback against Azerbaijan in World Cup qualifier
arts.sum: France complete a 3-1 comeback against Azerbaijan at the Tofiq Bahramov Republican Stadium on Sunday, finishing unbeaten on top of UEFA group D in World Cup qualifying.

arts.ttl: Mateta on target as France beat Azerbaijan
arts.sum: France rounded off their successful World Cup qualifying campaign with a 3-1 win over Azerbaijan in Baku.

arts.ttl: Why Kylian Mbappe is Not Playing for France vs. Azerbaijan
arts.sum: Mbappé will undergo further tests once he’s reported back to Madrid, with supporters hopeful that he hasn’t aggravated the ankle issue that kept him out for a relatively brief period at the start of the season. Mbappé’s five goals, including a brace in the 4–0 victory over Ukraine on Thursday, helped Les Bleus to top spot in Group D with a matchday remaining, meaning the 2018 world champions will be one of the 48 nations competing in North America next summer.
